For what i had read (in webs like this one), i thought a wiz would always crit for 2x base dmg, and it would just be the frecuency (chance to hit) scaling up all teh way from fury 1 to fury mastery 3.<P>But its not like that, with fury 1 it seems to have the same base to-hit chance, and a fixed 33%pct dmg bonus (i just got fury 1). I expect fury 2 to give 66% dmg bonus and 3 100% damage bonus (im not there yet).<P>And then fury mastery will increase the chance to hit while dmg will remain at 100%. Can aynone confirm this?<P>My point is: to produce a 14% extra damage (fury master 3 grants 14% to-thi chance of doing 100% extra dmg due to fury 3) (wich btw equates to a new weapon for a meleer in any expansion), a wizard must spend: 6 (general AA) + 2 (first fury) + 4 (second fury) + 7 (third fury) + 3 (first fury master) + 6 + (2nd fury master) + 9 (3rd fury master) = 37 AA. Im not sure at all ab this math, might be completely wrong. Can any one confirm this?. 37 AA is what, doing 60 from scracth 2 times?.. how many months of game play?<P>In contrast, having a Magician friend to summon one of those focus items will do 10% dmg bouns for 1 sec.<P>Also, it seems like fury 1 just gives you a fixed 33pct dmg increase insted of a random 1% to 66% as stated in the thread, wich turns to be exactly the same thing. Can anyone confirm this too? cause then 1st fury is worth nothing, just 2 AA to the bin. This would deny VI claims that innate crit does not lessen AA's,<P>I must be wrong somewhere, could some one tell me where?<P>Torok Palatox<BR>Erudite Sorcerer.
