Okay&#8230;<P>For the sake of argument, let&#8217;s say the base crit-rate is 2%.<P>In an EXP group, a wizard usually won&#8217;t nuke more than twice per mob unless something is going wrong.<P>So, a wizard will average one crit every 25 MOBs.<P>Of course, this is a statistical statement so a Wizard could crit twice in a row, or go 100 MOBs without one, but that should be the average.<P>Now, you can crit on a partial resist and do less damage than the spell would normally do also. Not every crit is spectacular and the spectacular ones don&#8217;t even double a spells damage.<P>If this little change destroys in-game balance, then that balance never existed in the first place.<P>Rthen Majere&#8217;s continual unfounded statements simply serve to prove that you can reach level 60 with a class and still not know what you&#8217;re talking about.<P>--------------------<P>Balance doesn&#8217;t always mean you getting more and/or others getting less. Sometimes you have to recognize that you should be the one to not get more, or to give something up.
