<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Rthen, I really admire your careful support of your positions.  Your presentation of essential documentation, combined with your elegant rhetoric leaves your opposition with absolutely no basis from which to argue.<P>Okay, now that we've taken care of my dose of sarcastic humor for the morning, let's get serious.  And oh, by the way, as I was so cordially informed when I had the nerve to actually post on 'your' magicians' board:  "This is not a flame, even though it might sound like one."<P>You seem terribly bent out of shape concerning wizard critical hits...and what can I say?  Your well-constructed arguments have convinced me.  They're totally destroying game balance...and to prove it, let's run the numbers, shall we?<P>Best available data indicates that a wizard has about a 2% chance (0.02) of scoring some form of critical cast.  If a critical cast hits, it adds between 1 and 66% to the damage.  Let's assume a linear distribution on damage adds, if for no other reason than a desire on Verant's part to reduce server load.  If I remember my statistics courses, the average on such a linear distribution is the average of the extremes, or, in this case, (1%+66%)/2 = 67%/2 = 33.5%. Since I'm supporting your argument that the critical casts are game destroying, let's round that up to 34%.  It's also simpler to figure.<P>That would make the long-term impact of critical casts the product of the frequency of occurrence and the average impact of an occurrence, or 0.02 x .34 = 0.0068.  In case you lost track of the zeroes, that's not a 68% increase...it's not a 6.8% increase...it's a game-busting 0.68% increase in wizards' overall damage. <P>Quoting:<BR>Rthen Majere  This is overpowering and it has destroyed the in-game balance <BR>End quote.<P>Sorry, my friend.  If that kind of damage increase is game-breaking, then Verant had better pull the Cannibalize, Pact, Clarity, Harvest, and yes, even the "Mod Rod" lines of spells from the game, because increasing a wizard's mana regen rate does a lot more for their damage in the long run than innate criticals ever will. <P>Moving on to your equally well-supported contention that mages need critical damage, or that the ability should be shared with all INT-caster clases--why?  Because it's something neat?  Show some reasons beyond simple one-sentence 'sound bites', if you would.<P>Hepzibah
