"I won't comment on your memory, Rethn...but before you continue, why don't you trot up to The Bazzar, and buy the new Mage spell "summon flamethrower" ? You know, the one that gives you +20% intensity to all flame-postings? Trust me, you need it...because this is one of the weakest and most pathetic attempted flames I've ever seen. And if it was intended as a rebuttal, and not a flame, it's even weaker."<P>I don't make a living "flaming" people.  I don't know enough about your sorry little life to construct a cute flame (nor do I care to know anything about your sorry little life). <P>"I note that, rather than commenting on my back-of-the envelope analysis, you come back to your forte..."Anybody who doesn't agree with me is an idiot!!!". If your point is so "Obvious" and so "self evident", then you should be able to show some proof that it's also valid. Let me guess...you couldn't find any analysis to support you, and your "summon supporting documentation" spell fizzled?"<P>In the real world we don't use /emote or spells to communicate or do much of anything, magic after all does not really work in the real world.  Since you seem to think magic and eq = reality I would suggest getting in touch with some profesisonal help since it seems that EQ has taken over your life.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>"1) Possible...even probable. Then again, damage and mobility are the two things a wizard is built for. We should be good at them."<P>Magicians are also "built" for damage.<P><BR>"I'll agree, all INT casters deserve something. Will you settle for a pet that has 7 extra HP per thousand? That's the same increase in power that you claim makes wizards so game-shattering. 7 extra damage per 1,000. Go back and look at the numbers I ginned up."<P>Your comparison is completley off base and illogical.  From what my friends level 57 wizard can do with the inate crits 1 spell in 30 seems to hit for double damage.  This complements Fury 1 and 2 and even 3 very well.  When she gets Fury 1 she will have the crit capabilties I have now at Fury 2.<P>"I thought the problem was that magicians were a broken class, with lousy nukes, useless summoning spells, and crippled pets. Now you tell me it's all "player perception"? That, I can cure for you...stop telling everybody your class sucks, and the public perception might change."<P><BR>Magicians telling the world they do not suck so much will not make one bit of difference.  The fact that Wizards can display decent damage though inate crits from level 11 and above will provide the player population with the preceptive evidence required to establish them again as "damage dealers" in EQ "society".  There is no such evidence for Magicians.<P>Comparing both classes at level 60 it becomes evident that Magiciansare the ed Mcmann's of EQ.<P>--------------------<P>Rthen Majere<BR>Arch Mage<BR>Master of the Orb<BR>Master of Fungus Grove
