<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Isn't it really all relative? <P>When EQ was young, it was very accepted that some characters were easy to level and some were not. <P>Easy to level, not as powerful later. <BR>Hard to level, better pay off. <P>Mage = Easier to level<BR>Wizard = Harder to level<P>So maybe the equation isn't as simple now. And so now they've made melee more powerful and they are still easier to level than casters (provided they group). <P>Maybe EQ is like Life. It isn't always totally fair. You give up something to get something. And some people seem to get more breaks than you do. <P>If a person wants to concentrate on Raids and "end game"  they shouldn't make a beastlord. And maybe add Mage (among others) to that list. <P>Every single class rocks in it's own way. And part of balancing might include finding something for Mages, and Beastlords and Shadowknights (ect) to do when they reach those high levels and find themselves unwanted in big groups and raids. Maybe THAT'S where balancing will come in. <P>Rthen, you seem very intelligent. Maybe you make such ridiculous statements just to get a lot of reaction. <P>It just seems obvious to me that if you play your class to 50 and don't like where it ended up in the food chain. You try a different class. We all know it's not that hard. And the game truly is more fun at mid levels. <P>If all that you care about is end game, then I think you might be playing the wrong class. Balancing might not mean that every class becomes all powerful in the raid situation. You can't have your cake and eat it too. You can't be a Mage for 50 levels then become a wizard. <P>I play 7 different classes. My wizard is most work of any of my characters to play. She takes the most strategy and has the smallest room for error.  When you MAKE the wizard it even tells you it's difficult. I fully expect to do more damage than a character who leveled alot easier. I will have earned it.  <P>You may not agree with me. You may not like what I say. I know you don't want to hear it. I didn't want to know my Beastlord was going to have it rough at the end either. But ANY pet class that has to deal damage is not going to be a shining star in end game.<P>--------------------<P>Taliana - Druid<BR>Montanna - Beastlord<BR>Steelcelt - Shaman<BR>Aimeesha - Wizard<BR>The Rathe - Stormhammer<BR>/Celts/ - Spellweavers
